# AI-DLC — the committed-vs-ignored split (workspace layout, re-rooted under aidlc/).
# Rule of thumb (vision §5.1): per-user session CURSORS and machine-local
# runtime/derived state are ignored; everything that is the shared work —
# method, registry, state, AUDIT (per-clone shards), artifacts — is committed.
#
# Per-user session cursors — ignored (two teammates legitimately point at
# different spaces/intents at once; committing them would dirty the tree on
# every /aidlc and have teammates fight over the cursor on each switch).
aidlc/active-space
aidlc/spaces/*/intents/active-intent
#
# Machine-local runtime / derived — ignored (regenerated per machine).
# The clone-id token names this clone's audit shard; it MUST stay machine-local
# (gitignored) or every clone from a commit would share a shard and git-conflict.
aidlc/.aidlc-clone-id
# Per-conversation session→intent map (resume rebind, P8): per-user runtime
# state keyed by Claude Code session_id, never shared truth.
aidlc/.aidlc-sessions/
aidlc/spaces/*/intents/*/runtime-graph.json
aidlc/spaces/*/intents/*/.aidlc-*
#
# COMMITTED (NOT ignored, listed here for the record — do NOT add ignore rules
# for these): aidlc/spaces/*/memory/** · aidlc/spaces/*/codekb/** ·
# aidlc/spaces/*/intents/intents.json · aidlc/spaces/*/intents/*/aidlc-state.md ·
# aidlc/spaces/*/intents/*/audit/*.md (the audit trail, committed as PER-CLONE
# SHARDS: each machine appends to audit/<host>-<clone>.md so git never merges
# concurrent appends — there is intentionally NO .gitattributes merge=union,
# which was proven to corrupt the multi-line audit blocks) ·
# aidlc/spaces/*/intents/*/<phase>/<stage>/*.md (artifacts + diary).
.claude/settings.local.json
.gstack/
